snippet.textDisplay:
A lil' tip for the next time you wanna create sharp lines with tapes while painting:

After adding the tape, generously paint over it completely using the original color of the wall (in this case white). Then, after letting the base dry, add the new color. Peel off the tape while the paint is still a bit wet. I promise nothing will run under the tape and the line will be crisp AF, no matter how cheap the tape it is!
